reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 3, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars great for artists
reviews.reviewText: i bought this ring light so i could have better lighting for drawing/recording my art. so far, i'm very happy with the quality! it's super user-friendly, light weight, and i appreciate the different light settings it comes with because it gives me more control over what looks best with different art pieces. i like the clamp - it's very strong but has a soft material on the inside of the clamp, so i'm not worried about it damaging my desk. also, it only takes up a small portion of space - way better than a ring light with a stand (at least for my needs). more importantly, the lighting from this ring light is super even, makes my art pop, and i just wish i would have bought this years ago! it does get a little warm after use, but nothing too warm to touch. overall (and especially for the price), this ring light is a major upgrade to my art setup and i highly recommend it! it's great for taking video, pictures, and creates a pleasant, even lighting for making art.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 1, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars WOW much smaller and yetmuch better than expected
reviews.reviewText: I love this little lamp, very sturdy with large and strong clamp....produces plenty of very bright, easily controlled and directed light!! Perfect @ a great price!! I recommend highly... it is much smaller than I expectedwhich turns out to be a very handy feature.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Nice light, but use a better power brick
reviews.reviewText: I use this lamp as a chair side reading light, clipped to the pole of a floor lamp. It’s compact, lightweight, and inconspicuous. The USB power brick always fit loosely in the wall socket. After almost two years of use, the lamp stopped working. I replaced the USB brick with a better quality one, and now the lamp is working again. Try this if your lamp is flickering or stops working. Otherwise, good value for a low price.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 31, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Using them for a pop-up painting & drawing exhibition!
reviews.reviewText: We setup a pop-up arts exhibition in kind of a dimly-lit space, and needed the aid of some lighting to show the artworks better. We gave these a try. The painting artworks were setup on easels, and we clamped the lights on the hooks on top of the easels. The longer neck allowed us to extend the lights outward to put a fairly even light on the paintings and drawings. With the 3 color settings and the ability to brighten or dim the light, the results are pretty good. The downside is since they operate on USB power, we had to get a bunch of charger blocks and extension cords to run the powers to where they are. I guess it would have been the same scenario if the lights could be plugged directly into regular sockets. We just wouldn't have to buy the charger blocks. It worked out fairly well for this exhibit.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 10, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Compact and bright
reviews.reviewText: I bought one for a reading corner in my basement and ended up buying a second for my bedroom. The lamp is flexible and can be bright for reading. It can also be dimmed if you're trying not to disturb others. The only limitation is that it is USB only and doesn't come with a plug. This didn't feel like a big deal given the price point and the ubiquity of USB plugs today.

reviews.reviewText: Very happy with it. The different light options work well and so overall I'm really happy with it.There are a lot of similar items and I think I only chose this one as the price was fair enough.
